8 PROPOSED SUBCOMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to Home and Community Based programs;
directing the Oklahoma Department of Human Services
10 to update and maintain a certain website; requiring
the Department to include a rating system, inspection
11 reports, substantiated complaints, and administrator
information; mandating annual updates from agencies;
12 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
13
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-1975 of Title 63, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. The Oklahoma Department of Human Services shall update and
21 maintain its Provider Search website that locates agencies that
22 provide services for the following Home and Community Based
23 programs:
24 1. Advantage Waiver;
Req. No. 16155 Page 1

1 2. Living Choice;
2 3. Medically Fragile Waiver; and
3 4. State Plan Personal Care (SPPC).
4 B. The website shall also include:
5 1. A rating system established by the Department or another
6 accredited licensing agency;
7 2. Inspection reports;
8 3. Substantiated complaints;
9 4. Administrator information; and
10 5. A link to the State Department of Health to be able to
11 report an issue with an agency.
12 C. The Department shall require agencies to update information
13 on the website annually.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
